2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20Charlie%20when%20I%20was%2028%20and%20Harry%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20later.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20girly%20girl%20with%20two%20boys%2C%20I%20had%20two%20options%3A%20either%20get%20left%20out%20or%20join%20in.%20I%20learned%20football%2C%20rugby%2C%20and%20cricket.%20I%20took%20them%20to%20watch%20airplanes%20take%20off%20at%20Heathrow.%20I'd%20collect%20them%20from%20school%2C%20and%20we'd%20have%20dinner%20around%20the%20table%20most%20evenings.%20These%20were%20precious%20times%20to%20hear%20them%20download%20about%20their%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECharlie%20went%20to%20boarding%20school%20at%2013%2C%20followed%20by%20Harry.%20I%20started%20working%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20making%20sure%20I%20still%20had%20time%20to%20see%20them%20on%20weekends.%20It%20was%20difficult%20to%20let%20them%20go.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20a%20big%20part%20of%20their%20lives%20and%20listening%20to%20what%20they%20had%20to%20say%20has%20always%20been%20a%20priority.%20Parents%20are%20busy%2C%20but%20I%20always%20had%2010%20minutes%20to%20sit%20down%2C%20go%20for%20a%20walk%2C%20or%20have%20a%20cup%20of%20coffee%20together%20%E2%80%94%20just%20to%20listen.%20I%20think%20it's%20had%20a%20positive%20effect%20on%20their%20development%20as%20adults.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229055f8a8-3505-4602-8cef-74f504ec178c%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20learn%20my%20children's%20interests%20so%20I%20can%20have%20useful%20conversations%20with%20them%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20boys%20are%20very%20close%2C%20they%20have%20always%20been%20different.%20Harry%20has%20been%20finance-oriented%20since%20he%20was%2014%2C%20while%20Charlie%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20career%20in%20sports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20never%20tried%20to%20make%20them%20into%20something%20they%20aren't.%20Instead%2C%20I%20embraced%20who%20they%20were%20and%20supported%20them%20in%20doing%20what%20they%20wanted.%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20shaped%20their%20career%20paths%2C%20I%20just%20tried%20to%20build%20their%20confidence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20they%20were%20kids%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20expose%20them%20to%20what%20they%20were%20interested%20in.%20Whatever%20they%20were%20interested%20in%2C%20I%20learned%20about%2C%20so%20I%20could%20discuss%20with%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20they%20were%20doing%20English%20exams%20at%20school%2C%20I%20would%20read%20the%20books%20they%20were%20studying%20so%20I%20could%20talk%20about%20them%20in%20the%20car.%20When%20Charlie%20showed%20an%20interest%20in%20sports%2C%20I%20learned%20all%20about%20Ronaldo.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20do%20the%20same%20now%20%E2%80%94%20learning%20about%20banking%20systems%20so%20I%20can%20talk%20to%20Harry%20about%20it%20on%20a%20walk.%20Sometimes%20it%20sounds%20like%20he%20is%20speaking%20a%20different%20language%20it's%20so%20technical.%20But%20now%20I've%20learned%20more%20about%20venture%20capital%2C%20I%20can%20ask%20him%20better%20questions%20and%20give%20him%20a%20different%20perspective.%20I%20listen%20to%20cricket%20on%20the%20radio%2C%20so%20that%20I%20can%20talk%20to%20Charlie%20about%20it.%20It's%20fantastic%20and%20gives%20us%20much%20more%20to%20talk%20about.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20also%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20show%20interest%20in%20what%20I%20love.%20Harry%20knows%20so%20much%20about%20Chanel%20and%20fashion.%20It's%20my%20passion.%20I%20think%20it's%20really%20important%20that%20they%20learn%20to%20listen%20as%20well%20as%20be%20heard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a649ba0-ab7d-48ec-ac0f-176dc1adbf42%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EGiving%20my%20kids%20space%20meant%20they%20came%20back%20to%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20our%20bond%20was%2