of%20the%20major%20ride-hailing%20and%20delivery%20apps.%20The%20company%20analyzed%20171%20million%20trips%20and%20%241.9%20billion%20worth%20of%20gig%20worker%20earnings%20to%20compile%20its%20findings%20for%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20Gridwise's%20finding.%20A%20company%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20Uber%20offers%20a%20suggested%20tip%20on%20food%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20most%20commonly%2015%25%20%E2%80%94%20though%20customers%20decide%20the%20amount.%20It%20also%20encourages%20customers%20to%20tip%20more%20during%20inclement%20weather%2C%20such%20as%20snow%20storms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20Instacart%20spokesperson%20called%20Gridwise's%20conclusion%20%26quot%3Binaccurate%20and%20misleading.%26quot%3B%20Instacart%20asks%20customers%20if%20they%20want%20to%20increase%20their%20tips%20when%20they%20give%20a%20shopper%20a%20five-star%20rating.%20Since%202022%2C%20the%20company%20has%20also%20offered%20to%20pay%20shoppers%20up%20to%20%2410%20when%20a%20customer%20takes%20their%20tip%20away%20after%20delivery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoorDash%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20findings%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETips%20have%20long%20been%20a%20big%20focus%20for%20gig%20workers.%20Some%20have%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20decide%20which%20orders%20to%20take%20depending%20on%20how%20much%20the%20tip%20is.%20But%20that%20can%20be%20risky%3A%20Some%20drivers%20for%20Walmart's%20Spark%20delivery%20service%20said%20last%20year%20that%20customers%20sometimes%20take%20back%20their%20tips%20after%20their%20order%20arrives%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tactic%20that%20the%20workers%20call%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-spark-drivers-say-tip-baiting-remains-a-problem-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etip%20baiting%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20apps%2C%20including%20Instacart%20and%20DoorDash%2C%20have%20countered%20that%20practice%20by%20shortening%20the%20time%20that%20customers%20have%20to%20adjust%20their%20tip%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202023%2C%20DoorDash%20started%20telling%20some%20customers%20that%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-tips-orders-take-longer-arrive-food-faster-slower-delivery-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorders%20might%20take%20longer%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20arrive%20if%20they%20didn't%20tip.%20A%20company%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time%20that%20DoorDash's%20gig%20workers%20can%20choose%20which%20orders%20they%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Uber%2C%20Lyft%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20Instacart%2C%20or%20another%20company%20as%20a%20gig%20worker%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20808-854-4501.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-most-of-food-delivery-driver-earnings-study-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740221222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8747a7bb3f854015d7402%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-most-of-food-delivery-driver-earnings-study-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gig%20workers%20for%20services%20like%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20Eats%20relied%20on%20tips%20for%20a%20majority%20of%20their%20earnings%20last%20year%2C%20a%20report%20from%20Gridwise%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-most-of-food-delivery-driver-earnings-study-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22She%20knew%20she%20might%20get%20Alzheimer's%20in%20her%2030s.%20That%20didn't%20make%20it%20any%20easier.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20photo%20of%20Jaime%20Bortz.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3b67cbfebcc4d029de45c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJaime%20Bortz%20at%20home%20in%20Buffalo%2C%20New%20York.%20At%2039%2C%20a%20few%20years%20since%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20Alzheimer's%2C%20her%20memory%20loss%20is%20accelerating.%3Cp%3EKate%20Warren%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jaime%20Bortz%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20she'd%20gently%20take%20hold%20of%20her%20dad's%20hand%20while%20they%20walked%20through%20the%20mall%20in%20Buffalo%2C%20New%20York.%20She'd%20guide%20him%20along%20to%20prevent%20him%20from%20getting%20lost%2C%20as%20if%20he%20were%20the%20child%2C%20she%20the%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20her%20dad%2C%20Steve%20Bortz%2C%20went%20to%20live%20in%20a%20nursing%20home.%20Jaime%2C%20a%20high%20schooler%20at%20the%20time%2C%20was%20embarrassed%20to%20tell%20her%20friends%20where%20her%20dad%20lived.%20She%20knew%20she%20never%20wanted%20to%20end%20up%20in%20a%20place%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20time%20is%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20Jaime%20to%20live%20at%20home.%20She's%2039%20now.%20As%20the%20clock%20ticks%20on%2C%20the%20gaps%20in%20her%20brain%20widen%2C%20and%20she%20becomes%20more%20confused.%20Memories%20are%20rapidly%20slipping%20away%2C%20much%20as%20they%20did%20for%20her%20dad.%20She%20forgets%20how%20to%20dress%20herself%2C%20can't%20speak%20in%20full%20sentences%2C%20and%20cries%20a%20lot%2C%20perhaps%20because%20she's%20still%20aware%20enough%20to%20be%20frustrated%20by%20what's%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaime's%20half-brother%20Todd%20went%20through%20this%20decline%20a%20decade%20ago.%20A%20father%20to%20three%20young%20kids%20at%20the%20time%2C%20he%20started%20forgetting%20how%20to%20drive%20his%20own%20bus%20route%2C%20often%20getting%20lost%20with%20passengers%20on%20board.%20In%20a%20matter%20of%20a%20few%20years%2C%20memories%20of%20who%20he%20married%2C%20what%20he%20liked%20to%20eat%2C%20and%20even%20%3Cspan%3Ehis%20own%20shy%20nature%3C%2Fspan%3E%20were%20erased.%20He%20died%20of%20sepsis%20at%2043.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Todd's%20brother%2C%20Aaron%2C%20died%20at%2040%2C%20with%20many%20of%20the%20same%20memory%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaime%2C%20Todd%2C%20and%20Aaron%20all%20inherited%20a%20rare%20PSEN1%20gene%20mutation%20from%20their%20father%20that%20guaranteed%20they'd%20develop%20Alzheimer's%20at%20a%20young%20age.%20They%20are%20members%20of%20an%20unlucky%20tribe%2C%20the%201%25%20of%20people%20with%20dementia%20who%20have%20early-onset%20familial%20Alzheimer's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20with%20the%20family%20history%2C%20no%20one%20believed%20that%20someone%20her%20age%20would%20have%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20Bortz%2C%20Jaime's%20mother%20and%20Steve's%20widow%2C%20told%20me%20when%20I%20visited%20her%20at%20home%20in%20Buffalo%20last%20year.%20By%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%26quot%3B%20she%20meant%20friends%2C%20family%2C%20even%20some%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehas%20been%20a%20default%20caretaker%20at%20every%20turn.%20As%20a%20young%20mom%2C%20she%20handled%20Steve's%20decline.%20Years%20later%2C%20she%20helped%20Todd's%20wife%2C%20Michelle%2C%20go%20through%20it.%20Now%2064%2C%20she's%20the%20anchor%20of%20a%20bustling%20household%2C%20caring%20for%20Jaime%20and%20her%209-year-old%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20feeling%20desperate%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20try%20to%20stay%20optimistic%20and%20positive%2C%20and%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20put%20on%20a%20harder%20exterior%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20to%20do%20what%20I%20got%20to%20do%20to%20get%20everybody%20through.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20is%20foreshadowing%20the%20burden%20many%20families%20will%20soon%20experience.%20An%20article%20published%20in%20Nature%20Medicine%20in%20January%20suggests%20America%20is%20set%20to%20weather%20a%20cascade%20of%20dementia%20cases%2C%20a%20doubling%20of%20Alzheimer's%20patients%20by%202060.%20It%20predicts%20that%20by%20then%2C%20the%20country%20will%20gain%201%20million%20new%20dementia%20patients%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222369%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mother%20and%20daughter%20sit%20in%20the%20kitchen%20and%20look%20straight%20at%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3b82d7bb3f854015bde00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221579%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBonnie%20Bortz%20(right)%2C%20Jaime's%20mom%2C%20is%20her%20caretaker.%20Bonnie%20noticed%20early%20signs%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20In%20her%20early%2030s%2C%20Jaime%20started%20repeating%20herself%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20kept%20misplacing%20her%20keys%20and%20phone.%3Cp%3EKate%20Warren%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFamilies%20like%20the%20Bortzes%20are%20rare%20and%20warrant%20attention.%20There%20are%20just%2045%2C000%20cases%20like%20theirs%20worldwide.%20This%20small%20circle%20of%20people%20can%20offer%20researchers%20a%20glimpse%20into%20how%20Alzheimer's%20develops.%20Because%20they%20develop%20the%20first%20signs%20at%20early%20ages%2C%20researchers%20can%20separate%20the%20disease%20itself%20from%20other%20issues%20common%20among%20older%20people%2C%20like%20heart%20disease%20or%20type%202%20diabetes.%20Early-onset%20cases%20have%20helped%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20class%20of%20Alzheimer's%20drugs%2C%20which%20have%20started%20to%20become%20available%20in%20recent%20years.%20While%20these%20antibody%20treatments%20don't%20cure%20the%20disease%2C%20they%20can%20slow%20its%20progression%2C%20buying%20families%20a%20little%20more%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there%20is%20much%20to%20learn.%20Researchers%20don't%20understand%20what%20causes%20the%20disease.%20Ultimately%2C%20there%20probably%20isn't%20just%20one%20kind%20of%20Alzheimer's%20that%20can%20be%20fixed%20by%20one%20single%20prescription.%20Families%20like%20the%20Bortzes%20show%20how%20far%20researchers%20still%20have%20to%20go%20in%20understanding%20dementia%20and%20developing%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20cancer%2C%26quot%3B%20Fred%20%26quot%3BRusty%26quot%3B%20Gage%2C%20who%20researches%20dementia%20and%20neurodegenerative%20diseases%20at%20the%20Salk%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20single%20disease.%20There%20are%20different%20forms%20of%20it%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20just%20genetic%20forms%20versus%20nongenetic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4f9fdd2-677a-4a34-b18c-86b8beff37be%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%2050%2F50%20shot%20at%20dementia%20in%20your%2030s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20knew%20something%20was%20wrong%20when%20Jaime%20moved%20back%20home%20in%20her%20early%2030s.%20She%20kept%20forgetting%20her%20keys%20and%20phone%20and%20repeated%20herself%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20repeating%20of%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20that%20was%20definitely%20something%20my%20husband%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20was%20subtle%2C%20little%20things.%26quot%3B%20Jaime%20lost%20the%20insurance%20job%20she'd%20had%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%20Finally%2C%20around%20the%20time%20of%20Jaime's%2036th%20birthday%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20agreed%20it%20was%20time%20to%20get%20Jaime%20tested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20type%20of%20dementia%20that%20runs%20in%20the%20Bortz%20family%20is%20genetically%20preordained.%20Someone%20who%20inherits%20a%20genetic%20mutation%20from%20one%20of%20their%20parents%20will%20almost%20certainly%20develop%20dementia%2C%20progressively%20forgetting%20what%20they've%20learned%20over%20a%20lifetime.%20It%20generally%20starts%20with%20short-term%20memories%2C%20then%20expands%20to%20erase%20aspects%20of%20who%20they%20are%20and%20how%20they%20function.%20People%20with%20this%20early-onset%20genetic%20form%20of%20the%20disease%20suffer%20a%20much%20earlier%20and%20faster%20descent%20than%20people%20with%20%26quot%3Bregular%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20sporadic%2C%20Alzheimer's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGage%20says%20that%20to%20categorically%20separate%20nongenetic%20forms%20of%20Alzheimer's%20from%20the%20forms%20that%20families%20like%20the%20Bortzes%20have%20is%20naive.%20Each%20person's%20genetics%20shape%20their%20case.%20%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20roughly%2060%25%20of%20people%20who%20carry%20two%20copies%20of%20the%20APOE4%20gene%20will%20develop%20Alzheimer's%20during%20their%20lifetime%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20(The%20actor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchris-hemsworth-doesnt-have-dementia-isnt-retiring-alzheimers-risk-gene-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChris%20Hemsworth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20carries%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20gene%20from%20each%20of%20his%20parents%2C%20has%20been%20open%20about%20his%20%26quot%3B4-4%26quot%3B%20status.)%20%3Cspan%3EOther%20folks%2C%20through%20some%20kind%20of%20genetic%20luck%2C%20can%20carry%20the%20same%20genes%2C%20and%20may%20even%20develop%20the%20amyloid%20plaques%20or%20tau%20tangles%20characteristic%20of%20Alzheimer's%20and%20yet%20never%20show%20signs%20of%20dementia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Of%20Steve's%20four%20children%2C%20only%20one%20did%20not%20develop%20his%20rare%20form%20of%20early%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20dozens%20of%20genes%20that%20have%20been%20found%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20Alzheimer's%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Gage%20said.%20Few%20of%20them%20single-handedly%20control%20a%20person's%20cognitive%20destiny.%20If%20most%20dementia%20diagnoses%20are%20colored%20in%20shades%20of%20gray%2C%20the%20Bortzes'%20cases%20are%20harshly%20black%20and%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20image%20of%20Bonnie%20Bortz%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3b6217bb3f854015bdd89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20say%20Bonnie's%20family%20is%20rare%20and%20warrants%20attention%20as%20the%20number%20of%20Alzheimer's%20cases%20is%20set%20to%20double%20in%20the%20US%20by%202060%2C%20with%20few%20%E2%80%94%20if%20any%20%E2%80%94%20reliable%20treatments%20in%20sight.%3Cp%3EKate%20Warren%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20as%20life%20at%20the%20Bortzes'%20house%20was%20getting%20more%20difficult%2C%20new%20Alzheimer's%20drugs%20were%20starting%20to%20become%20available.%20The%20blockbuster%20was%20Leqembi%2C%20a%20Japanese%20drug%20brought%20to%20market%20in%20the%20US%2C%20designed%20to%20clear%20out%20the%20clumps%20of%20protein%2C%20or%20amyloid%20plaques%2C%20that%20form%20between%20brain%20cells%20in%20people%20with%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20drugs%20haven't%20been%20found%20to%20halt%20or%20prevent%20the%20disease%2C%20but%20data%20from%20one%20of%20Leqembi's%20clinical%20trials%20suggested%20it%20could%20slow%20progression%20down%20by%20about%2027%25.%20In%20practical%20terms%2C%20that%20means%20people%20might%20gain%20an%20extra%20four%20or%20five%20months%20of%20independence%20%E2%80%94%20of%20driving%2C%20perhaps%2C%20or%20cooking%2C%20shopping%2C%20dressing%20themselves%2C%20and%20remembering%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pessimist%20would%20look%20at%20the%20data%20as%20it%20stands%20and%20say%3A%20'Well%2C%20we%20tried%20that.%20It%20obviously%20doesn't%20work%20very%20well%2C%20so%20maybe%20we%20should%20start%20looking%20at%20something%20else%2C'%26quot%3B%20Gage%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaime%20was%20on%20early%20Medicare%20for%20her%20disability.%20Legally%20she%20was%20still%20allowed%20to%20drive%2C%20but%20her%20mom%20took%20her%20keys%20away%20after%20she%20failed%20a%20driving%20evaluation%20funded%20by%20the%20Alzheimer's%20Association.%20It%20was%20getting%20harder%20to%20remember%20daily%20minutia%2C%20like%20the%20fact%20that%20her%20daughter%20likes%20peanut%20butter%20toast%20now%2C%20or%20how%20to%20put%20a%20paper%20filter%20into%20a%20coffee%20maker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Bonnie%20decided%20not%20to%20put%20Jaime%20on%20antibody%20drugs.%20She%20knew%20that%20they%20presented%20a%20small%20risk%20of%20brain%20bleeds%20and%20that%20Jaime%2C%20because%20she's%20a%20woman%20and%20because%20of%20her%20genetics%2C%20would%20be%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20developing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20cause%20more%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20said.%20In%202023%2C%20Jaime%20was%20developing%20some%20muscle%20jerks%2C%20prompted%20by%20one%20of%20the%20other%20medications%20she%20was%20on.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20seen%20these%20medications%20help%20her%20in%20any%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20said.%20%26quot%3BNot%20with%20memory%2C%20not%20with%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20focusing%20on%20drugs%20that%20target%20amyloid%20plaques%2C%20scientists%20are%20starting%20to%20try%20new%20tactics.%20More%20than%20100%20new%20Alzheimer's%20drugs%20are%20in%20later-stage%20clinical%20trials.%20If%20those%20trials%20are%20successful%2C%20the%20drugs%20could%20become%20available%20to%20patients%20in%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20years.%20They%20include%20therapies%20designed%20to%20target%20neuronal%20tau%20tangles%2C%20which%20pulverize%20and%20kill%20brain%20cells%20from%20the%20inside%2C%20and%20others%20that%20go%20after%20the%20inflammation%20tied%20to%20Alzheimer's.%20Increasingly%2C%20doctors%20are%20wondering%20whether%20the%20anti-inflammatory%20effects%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedicine.washu.edu%2Fnews%2Fstudy-identifies-benefits-risks-linked-to-popular-weight-loss-drugs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGLP-1%20drugs%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20Ozempic%20and%20Mounjaro%20may%20prove%20effective%20against%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20hope%20that%20we'd%20get%20to%20a%20good%20point%20where%20we%20look%20at%20where%20you%20are%20in%20the%20disease%20and%20we%20can%20fine-tune%20a%20cocktail%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lindsay%20Hohsfield%2C%20an%20Alzheimer's%20researcher%20and%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20who%20cofounded%20a%20nonprofit%20called%20Youngtimers%20to%20support%20families%20like%20the%20Bortzes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bortz%20family%20sitting%20in%20a%20living%20room%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a3b6e2bfebcc4d029de476%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJaime%20is%20starting%20to%20forget%20things%2C%20like%20how%20her%209-year-old%20daughter%20likes%20her%20toast.%3Cp%3EKate%20Warren%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f16fb902-9de8-4969-85e2-de2e52f7d8bd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20build%20a%20brain%20back%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJaime's%20condition%20has%20progressed%20dramatically%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20When%20I%20visited%20her%20at%20home%20in%20snowy%20Buffalo%20in%20early%202024%2C%20it%20was%20harder%20to%20tell%20something%20was%20amiss.%20She%20could%20carry%20on%20a%20simple%20conversation%2C%20exchanging%20pleasantries%20with%20a%20new%20houseguest%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20you%20spent%20more%20than%20a%20few%20minutes%20with%20her%2C%20you%20might%20notice%20her%20start%20to%20repeat%20questions%20(%26quot%3BWhere%20do%20you%20live%20again%3F%26quot%3B)%20or%20variations%20of%20them.%20Sometimes%2C%20she'd%20nod%20and%20quickly%20backtrack%2C%20insisting%20she%20already%20knew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReminiscing%20about%20old%20memories%2C%20like%20her%20favorite%20'90s%20TV%20shows%20or%20her%20pink%20prom%20dress%2C%20was%20much%20easier%20than%20recalling%20newly%20acquired%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20how%20her%20speech%20therapy%20was%20going%2C%20and%20she%20turned%20to%20her%20mom%20blankly.%20I%20can't%20know%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20her%20mind%2C%20but%20it%20seemed%20like%20she%20was%20scanning%20our%20faces%20for%20hints%20about%20how%20to%20answer%20and%20where%20the%20conversation%20should%20go%20next.%20Bonnie%20sensed%20the%20difference%20in%20her%20daughter%2C%20in%20the%20way%20a%20mother%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20sitting%20with%20me%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20her%20SUV%2C%20Bonnie%20pointed%20out%20Jaime's%20repetition.%20That%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20is%20what%20it's%20like%20everyday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie's%20been%20there%20through%20it%20all%2C%20managing%20the%20appointments%2C%20fighting%20to%20get%20Medicare%20payments%2C%20and%20evaluating%20which%20drugs%20and%20treatments%20to%20put%20her%20daughter%20on%20and%20which%20to%20skip.%20Driving%20often%20gives%20her%20some%20of%20her%20few%20solo%20moments%20of%20the%20day.%20She%20relishes%20going%20to%20work%2C%20rare%20time%20by%20herself.%20Recently%20she%20hired%20Michelle%2C%20Todd's%20wife%2C%20as%20an%20aide%20%E2%80%94%20a%20familiar%20face%20who%20can%20come%20help%20take%20care%20of%20Jaime%20for%20about%2010%20hours%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20tries%20to%20keep%20thoughts%20of%20the%20future%20to%20a%20minimum.%20Jaime's%20asked%20her%2C%20many%20times%2C%20not%20to%20put%20her%20in%20a%20nursing%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20pray%20to%20God%20it%20doesn't%20get%20to%20that%20point%2C%20because%20I%20would%20hate%20to%20do%20that%20to%20my%20daughter%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20that%20being%20said%2C%20I%20am%20older.%20I%20don't%20know.%20I%20just%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20doesn't%20know%20how%20Jaime's%20condition%20will%20develop%20and%20what%20kind%20of%20support%20she'll%20require.%20Jaime%20has%20told%20Bonnie%20that%20her%20biggest%20fears%20are%20the%20nursing%20home%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20difficult%20thing%20about%20Alzheimer's%2C%20all%20brain%20diseases%2C%20if%20you%20truly%20wanted%20to%20reverse%2C%20you%20would%20also%20not%20only%20have%20to%20clear%20out%20disease%2C%20you'd%20actually%20have%20to%20build%20the%20brain%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Nathaniel%20Chin%2C%20the%20medical%20director%20at%20the%20Wisconsin%20Alzheimer's%20Disease%20Research%20Center.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20an%20infection%20where%20if%20you%20identify%20it%2C%20you%20kill%20it%2C%20you%20go%20back%20to%20being%20yourself.%20I%20mean%2C%20the%20disease%20has%20destroyed%20parts%20of%20your%20brain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221865%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20family%20photo%20album%20is%20faced%20open%20on%20a%20recliner%20chair.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ad17d2eb4be2fff9a47a69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222798%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBonnie%20keeps%20photo%20albums%20around%20to%20reminisce%20about%20new%20and%20old%20memories%3Cp%3EKate%20Warren%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0d0591d-c0d1-4c9b-a181-b91617d46782%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHoping%20for%20a%20cure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20understands%20there's%20not%20much%20you%20can%20do%20to%20stop%20this%20disease.%20That%20doesn't%20stop%20her%20from%20being%20a%20mom%20%E2%80%94%20from%20trying%20to%20do%20something%2C%20anything%2C%20to%20help%20her%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20man%20sometimes%20comes%20to%20her%20house%20for%2010-minute%20sessions%20of%20cold%20laser%20therapy%2C%20designed%20to%20nourish%20and%20energize%20Jaime's%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20tells%20me%2C%20laughing%20out%20loud%2C%20probably%20realizing%20how%20ridiculous%20it%20sounds.%20Still%2C%20there's%20a%20quiet%20optimism.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20me%20is%20like%2C%20well%2C%20maybe%20we%20should%20keep%20trying%2C%20you%20know%3F%20As%20a%20mom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%20Bonnie%20joined%20an%20online%20support%20group%20for%20families%20with%20early-onset%20familial%20Alzheimer's.%20There%20she%20got%20sucked%20into%20another%20tantalizing%20promise%20that%20a%20product%20could%20somehow%20help%20Jaime.%20She%20ended%20up%20sending%20about%20%24600%20to%20a%20man%20offering%20specialty%20herbal%20supplements%20before%20she%20realized%20he'd%20never%20send%20her%20any%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20yourself%20suckered%20in%20because%20you%20want%20to%20believe%20that%20there's%20something%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonnie%20said.%20She's%20also%20ordered%20expensive%20memory%20supplements%20advertised%20on%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20moment%20of%20desperation%2C%20while%20Todd%20was%20in%20decline%20in%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20Michelle%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Dr.%20Phil%2C%20begging%20for%20his%20help.%20Maybe%20this%20wasn't%20really%20Alzheimer's%2C%20she%20wrote.%20Maybe%2C%20hopefully%2C%20it%20was%20some%20other%20rare%2C%20undiagnosed%20condition%20that%20could%20be%20cured%20once%20it%20could%20be%20properly%20identified.%20%26quot%3BIt%20sounds%20stupid%2C%20but%20I%20see%20that%20he%20does%20all%20these%20different%20testings%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%3Cspan%3EDeep%20down%2C%20she%20knew%20she%20wouldn't%20hear%20back%2C%20and%20knew%20he%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20help.%20Still%2C%20s%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe's%20contacted%20Dr.%20Phil%20a%20few%20times%20since%20then%2C%20including%20once%20recently%2C%20worrying%20about%20what's%20in%20store%20for%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20throughline%20is%20a%20flicker%20of%20hope.%20Isn't%20there%20something%20that%20can%20help%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20girl%20hugs%20a%20dog%20in%20the%20living%20room%20as%20her%20grandmother%20looks%20through%20a%20family%20album.%5C%22%20charset%3