2content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Airmen%20and%20guardians%20at%20a%20graduation%20parade%20at%20Joint%20Base%20San%20Antonio-Lackland%2C%20Texas%2C%20October%2017%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b84f2a6630eb10385d306f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAirmen%20and%20guardians%20at%20a%20graduation%20parade%20in%20Texas%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EUS%20Space%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Space%20Force%20needs%20a%20%26quot%3Bwarfighting%20ethos%26quot%3B%20to%20compete%20with%20China%20in%20space%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFailure%20to%20adapt%20could%20threaten%20the%20force's%20long-term%20chances%20of%20success%20in%20the%20space%20domain%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Space%20Force%20also%20lacks%20a%20clearly%20defined%20role%20and%20resources%2C%20the%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Space%20Force%20needs%20a%20change%20in%20mindset%20and%20increased%20funding%20to%20compete%20with%20China%20in%20the%20space%20domain%2C%20two%20retired%20US%20colonels%20argued%20in%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mitchellaerospacepower.org%2Fapp%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FEnsuring-a-Spacepower-Advantage-in-Prolonged-Competition-WEB.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20for%20Aerospace%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20which%20was%20released%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20summarizes%20the%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20from%20a%20two-day%20workshop%20held%20in%20October%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute's%20Spacepower%20Advantage%20Center%20of%20Excellence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20event%20brought%20together%2055%20space%20experts%20to%20examine%20the%20Space%20Force%20Chief%20of%20Space%20Operations'%20theory%20of%20success%20%E2%80%94%20called%20%26quot%3BCompetitive%20Endurance%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20against%20a%20set%20of%20potential%20crises%20over%20the%20next%2025%20years%2C%20including%20the%20Russian%20deployment%20of%20a%20nuclear%20antisatellite%20weapon%20and%20an%20attempted%20Chinese%20space%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workshop%20found%20that%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Space%20Force%20was%20not%20well%20understood%20by%20many%20Americans%20and%20that%20it%20lacked%20resources%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bwarfighting%20ethos%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20new%20report%20said%20threatened%20its%20long-term%20chances%20of%20success%20against%20China%20in%20the%20space%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSystemic%20issues%20exist%20within%20the%20Space%20Force%20and%20Department%20of%20Defense%20that%20threaten%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Space%20Force%20in%20a%20long-term%20competition%20with%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Charles%20Galbreath%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Space%20Force%20colonel%2C%20and%20Jennifer%20Reeves%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Air%20Force%20colonel%2C%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChief%20among%20these%20are%3A%20inadequate%20authorities%20and%20resources%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20clearly%20defined%20and%20understood%20roles%20and%20missions%2C%20and%20the%20need%20for%20increased%20warfighting%20ethos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrawing%20on%20the%20workshop's%20findings%2C%20the%20authors%2C%20both%20senior%20fellows%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%2C%20called%20on%20Congress%20to%20increase%20funding%20to%20the%20USSF%20and%20loosen%20policy%20restrictions%20to%20allow%20the%20deployment%20of%20offensive%20and%20defensive%20weapons%2C%20which%20they%20said%20would%20enable%20the%20force%20to%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20a%20stronger%20posture%2C%20capable%20of%20deterring%20hostile%20actions%20and%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20urged%20the%20force%20to%20develop%20educational%20and%20training%20programs%20that%20aimed%20to%20%26quot%3Bfoster%20an%20assertive%2C%20warfighting%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20Space%20Force%20members%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20Guardians%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bmust%20see%20themselves%20as%20warfighters%20and%20project%20a%20war-winning%20ethos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Galbreath%20and%20Reeves%20praised%20the%20%26quot%3Bthree%20tenets%20of%20Competitive%20Endurance%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20avoiding%20operational%20surprise%2C%20denying%20first-mover%20advantage%2C%20and%20undertaking%20responsible%20counter-space%20campaigning%20%E2%80%94%20they%20said%20the%20theory%20did%20not%20%26quot%3Bnormalize%20space%20as%20a%20warfighting%20domain%26quot%3B%20or%20allow%20Guardians%20to%20%26quot%3Bpursue%20victory%20and%20space%20superiority%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20they%20said%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20public%20and%20Congress%20to%20grasp%20its%20military%20importance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20loophole%20is%20not%20addressed%2C%20the%20Space%20Force%20and%20U.S.%20Space%20Command%20could%20find%20itself%20in%20a%20death%20spiral%20of%20waning%20support%20and%20funding%2C%20ultimately%20precluding%20the%20fielding%20of%20capabilities%20and%20conducting%20of%20operations%20necessary%20to%20secure%20U.S.%20interests%20in%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Space%20Force%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bas%20China%20and%20Russia%20accelerate%20the%20development%20of%20counter-space%20capabilities%2C%20the%20need%20for%20a%20well-resourced%20Space%20Force%20has%20never%20been%20more%20critical.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20Guardians%20remain%20committed%20to%20ensuring%20space%20superiority%20while%20safeguarding%20the%20long-term%20stability%20and%20sustainability%20of%20the%20domain%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaj.%20Gen.%20Timothy%20Sejba%2C%20commander%20of%20Space%20Training%20and%20Readiness%20Command%20(STARCOM)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spaceforce.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3524481%2Fstarcom-leaders-warfighting-mindset-guardian-spirit-key-for-future-force%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20that%20a%20warfighting%20mindset%20was%20vital%20to%20the%20USSF's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20attendees%20at%20the%20Air%20%26amp%3B%20Space%20Forces%20Association's%202023%20Air%2C%20Space%20%26amp%3B%20Cyber%20Conference%2C%20Sejba%2C%20then%20Brigadier%20General%2C%20said%20that%20STARCOM's%20mission%20was%20to%20instill%20the%20warfighting%20mindset%20in%20every%20Space%20Force%20recruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20the%20Space%20Force%20is%20only%20four%20years%20old%2C%20we've%20built%20the%20warfighting%20mindset%20for%20almost%2040%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bcritical%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20force%20to%20train%20%26quot%3Blike%20we%20potentially%20have%20to%20fight%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20exists%20in%20other%20domains%20and%20other%20services%2C%20but%20it's%20one%20that%20we%20just%20haven't%20necessarily%20had%20to%20put%20into%20place%20for%20space%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20have%20long%20warned%20of%20growing%20international%20threats%20facing%20the%20US%20in%20the%20space%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-fast-becoming-amilitary-risk-space-us-space-force-chief-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPolitico%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20October%2C%20Gen.%20B.%20Chance%20Saltzman%2C%20the%20Chief%20of%20Space%20Operations%2C%20said%20China%20was%20developing%20counter-space%20capabilities%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bmind-boggling%26quot%3B%20pace%20and%20was%20of%20particular%20concern%20for%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Plumb%2C%20a%20former%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20defense%20for%20space%20policy%2C%20also%20warned%20in