rst%20home.%20He%20said%20it%20profited%20about%20%2430%2C000%2C%20which%20he%20split%20with%20his%20business%20partner%20at%20the%20time.%20Before%20the%20end%20of%20that%20summer%2C%20he%20purchased%20two%20more%20flips%20and%20left%20insurance%20to%20work%20in%20real%20estate%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20his%20success%20flipping%2C%20and%20later%20wholesaling%2C%20helped%20him%20pay%20off%20his%20debt%20in%20two%20years%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20much%20else%20out%20there%20where%20you%20can%20make%20lump%20sum%20checks%20to%20help%20you%20pay%20off%20that%20debt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHart%20now%20works%20alongside%20a%20different%20business%20partner%2C%20Mike%20Gorius.%20They%20formed%20an%20official%20business%20partnership%20in%202024%20under%20the%20Joe%20Homebuyer%20franchise%20and%2C%20in%20their%20first%20full%20year%20working%20together%2C%20did%2050%20transactions%20between%20wholesales%2C%20wholetails%2C%20and%20flips.%20They%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investors-share-their-strategy-flip-and-buy-rentals-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eown%20more%20than%2020%20rental%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20short-%2C%20mid-%2C%20and%20long-term%2C%20in%20the%20Lousiville%20area.%20BI%20verified%20their%20property%20ownership%20and%20deal%20history%20by%20looking%20at%20settlement%20statements%20and%20closing%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221246%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mike%20gorius%20kevin%20hart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8af866630eb10385d3d49%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBusiness%20partners%20Mike%20Gorius%20and%20Kevin%20Hart.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Mike%20Gorius%20and%20Kevin%20Hart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20agree%20that%20rookie%20investors%20should%20consider%20starting%20with%20a%20flip%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bquick%20capital%20boost%20to%20help%20you%20get%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investors-share-their-strategy-flip-and-buy-rentals-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo-pronged%20real%20estate%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20involves%20flipping%20and%20wholesaling%20to%20bring%20in%20cash%2C%20and%20then%20buying%20and%20holding%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20flipping%20homes%2C%20there's%20always%20risk%20involved.%20To%20minimize%20risk%20and%20avoid%20losing%20money%20on%20your%20first%20flip%2C%20Hart%20and%20Gorius%20highlighted%20three%20costly%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Hiring%20the%20first%20contractor%20you%20find.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUnless%20you're%20planning%20on%20doing%20all%20of%20the%20renovation%20work%20yourself%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20need%20to%20work%20with%20a%20general%20contractor%20%E2%80%94%20and%20finding%20the%20right%20person%20for%20the%20job%20is%20key%20to%20a%20successful%20flip.%20This%20is%20the%20person%20you'll%20be%20relying%20on%20to%20transform%20a%20fixer-upper%20into%20a%20marketable%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvoid%20selecting%20%26quot%3Bsome%20random%20contractor%20you%20find%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BYou%20definitely%20don't%20want%20to%20hire%20the%20cheapest%20one%20you%20find.%20They're%20probably%20cheap%20and%20available%20for%20a%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20interview%20multiple%20contractors%2C%20call%20references%2C%20and%20look%20at%20their%20previous%20work.%20The%20more%20due%20diligence%2C%20the%20better%20off%20you'll%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20there%20are%20residential%20contractors%20and%20contractors%20who%20work%20with%20investors.%20You%20want%20to%20work%20with%20the%20latter%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20understand%20what%20flippers%20are%20looking%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Biting%20off%20more%20than%20you%20can%20chew.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20take%20on%20a%20project%20that's%20way%20bigger%20than%20you%20can%20handle%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20it's%20easier%20said%20than%20done%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20draw%20inspiration%20from%20HGTV%20shows%20that%20tend%20to%20feature%20full%20gut%20renovations.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20what%20you%20want%20on%20your%20first%20flip.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20was%20starting%20from%20scratch%20in%20Louisville%2C%20he%20said%20he'd%20target%20a%203-bedroom%2C%201-bath%20ranch-style%20house%20that%20could%20use%20cosmetic%20upgrades%3A%20%26quot%3BFloors%2C%20paint%2C%20kitchen%20cabinets%2C%20update%20the%20bathroom%20and%20a%20few%20minor%20things%20like%20light%20fixtures%20and%20call%20it%20a%20day.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20start%20a%20huge%20construction%20project%20when%20you%20have%20no%20experience%20doing%20construction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStick%20to%20the%20basics%2C%20added%20Gorius%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20pretend%20that%20you're%20the%20one%20moving%20into%20this%20house%20and%20start%20putting%20finishes%20on%20there%20that%20are%20overpriced%20or%20don't%20make%20sense.%20Stick%20with%20what%20works%2C%20talk%20to%20contractors%2C%20and%20walk%20other%20people's%20flips%20to%20see%20what%20finishes%20and%20paint%20colors%20and%20materials%20they're%20using%2C%20because%20they're%20doing%20that%20for%20a%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20goal%20with%20a%20flip%20is%20to%20create%20a%20home%20that%20appeals%20to%20the%20most%20amount%20of%20people%20possible%2C%20which%20means%20neutral%20colors%20and%20flooring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20if%20you're%20doing%20a%20lot%20of%20flips%2C%20flipping%20is%20a%20pretty%20boring%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20using%20the%20same%20paint%20colors%2C%20you're%20using%20similar%20flooring.%20Whatever's%20in%20style%20that%20year%2C%20we're%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20for%20the%20next%20five%20houses%2C%20this%20is%20what%20we're%20doing.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Running%20your%20numbers%20too%20optimistically.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAssume%20the%20project%20will%20cost%20more%20money%20and%20take%20more%20time%20than%20you%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGet%20really%20good%20at%20running%20your%20numbers%2C%20and%20be%20realistic%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hart%2C%20who%20built%20his%20own%20flipping%20calculator%20in%20Excel.%20That%20means%2C%20if%20you're%20running%20comps%20and%20see%20that%20one%20home%20in%20your%20market%20sold%20for%20%24250%2C000%20but%20the%20rest%20are%20selling%20for%20%24220%2C000%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can't%20get%20too%20excited%20and%20think%2C%20'my%20house%20is%20going%20to%20be%20worth%20250.'%20More%20likely%2C%20it'll%20be%20220%20or%20230.%20Don't%20try%20to%20force%20the%20numbers%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllow%20yourself%20a%20financial%20cushion%20because%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20new%20flipper%2C%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20inevitably%20is%20going%20to%20go%20wrong%20or%20you're%20going%20to%20miss%20something%20in%20the%20rehab%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20always%20happens.%20You%20can't%20go%20out%20there%20and%20project%20a%20flip%20is%20going%20to%20make%20%2410%2C000%20off%20the%20bat%2C%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%2C%20you%20buy%20it%20and%20miss%20this%20%2410%2C000%20foundation%20issue%20and%20now%20you're%20in%20the%20hole.%20So%20you%20just%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20you're%20buying%20correctly%20and%20getting%20your%20rehab%20cost%20as%20accurate%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-flipping-mistakes-avoid-common-costly-real-estate-tips-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740220201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F